title: Hemlington murder investigation: Four arrested after man stabbed
title_page: Hemlington murder investigation: Four arrested after man stabbed - BBC News
maintext:
Four people have been arrested after a man was fatally stabbed.
The attack is believed to have happened shortly after midnight at a property in Fonteyn Court, Hemlington, Middlesbrough, and the 28-year-old died at the scene.
Cleveland Police has now arrested two men, aged 27 and 43, on suspicion of murder.
Another man, 38, and a 19-year-old woman are being held on suspicion of assisting an offender.
